cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the recognition of handwritten characters using machine learning models, specifically convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of transfer learning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with natural language processing, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of neural networks also falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
